ustice for those who previously had been excluded. Richly illustrated with case examples through intermediaries’ own descriptions of their work, the book also includes feedback from justice system personnel and over 70 judges. This unique book provides a comprehensive explanation of how intermediaries work in practice and gives ‘behind the scenes’ insights into the criminal process. It will be of interest to practitioners and the wider public in England and Wales and encourage consideration of the scheme elsewhere.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aWitnessesxServices forzGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh1 aThomas of Cwmgiedd, Lord, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWoolfson, Richard, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Complete eBook-Package 2015z978311119642840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447326076423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447326076/original  a978-3-11-119642-8  Bristol University Press Complete eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK